      • setAddress

        public Interface.Builder setAddress(InterfaceAddress address)
        Set the primary address of the interface.
        The Interface.getAllAddresses() method of the built Interface will return a set containing the primary address and secondary addresses.
        The node will accept traffic whose destination IP belongs is among any of the addresses of any of the interfaces. The primary address is the one used by default as the source IP for traffic sent out the interface. A secondary address is another address potentially associated with a different subnet living on the interface. The interface will reply to ARP for the primary or any secondary IP.
